{"text": "“Britain was overtaken not only in gross output but also in output per worker. It lost its lead in technological innovation.”", "author": "Thomas Sowell,"}
{"text": "“Outside the world of education, few would be confident, or even comfortable, claiming that it is a lack of self-esteem which leads to felonies or its presence which leads to Nobel Prizes. Yet American schools are permeated with the idea that selfesteem precedes performance, rather than vice-versa. The very idea that self-esteem is something earned, rather than being a pre-packaged handout from the school system, seems not to occur to many educators.”", "author": "Thomas Sowell,"}
