{"text": "“In many countries – perhaps most countries – the establishment of law and order over large regions was a long and arduous process. Yet those who today advocate that government's economic role is to preserve the essential framework of law and order, leaving more specific economic decisions to the marketplace, are accused of saying that government should \"do nothing\" – even though (1) it took centuries to accomplish what is today called \"nothing\" and (2) that \"nothing\" has brought widespread economic beliefs to great numbers of human beings.”", "author": "Thomas Sowell,"}
